<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>To the Scythe,<br>
<br>
After careful consideration, and in talking with Ilharess Kerridwynn and Demaste, I would wish to be part of your family. I have little to offer but my magics, and wisdom if any should seek that. I find that I am not the young innocent I once was, that all has come to pass for a reason. My footsteps lead me to your door for a reason, and maybe I shall find out what that is. Then again, maybe not.<br>
For those of you who read this, I am a Yath’tallar of the 55th rank. I have made my peace with the creator of my race, and no longer choose to follow the path he has deemed for me. I know not what else you of the Scythe might wish to know, there is little to tell. <br>
At the moment I seek a place to heal old wounds, make friends, and continue on the path my Quar’valsharess has chosen for me. <br>
If any of you have any questions for me, about my decision, I would gladly take the time to answer them.<br>
<br>
<br>
~Ankhami Hateborn~<br>
Priestess of the 55th rank<br>
Bane of Innourruk</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Slowly she reread over the parchment, it was not as eloquent as she was used to but, it would suffice, and she was somewhat in a hurry, she felt the aloneness creeping in, the voices in her head were so sparse, she wanted to be needed again. Folding the pristine white parchment she dripped the white wax on the closing, placing her seal, imprinting her seal, a beautifully scrolled <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>AH</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on the now cooling wax. Upon the front she penned <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>‘The Scythe’</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in flowing bold script. Leaving her room, she headed down the stairs to the main foyer of the inn, she paid one of the urchins to run the parchment to the Harvesters of Darkness halls. Returning to her room, she awaited an answer. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.2guys.net/sig2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <br>
